          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p><placeName>Zanesville</placeName>
                                        <date>May 27 53</date>. <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee>
                                        <sic>Revent</sic> Sir.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName role="author">W. Dryfus</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Zanesville</placeName>, <date>May
                                                  27, 1853</date>.</p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>, Reverend Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dearest friend:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Since I have written to you without
                                        re-<lb/>ceiving any news. I again take the liberty to write
                                        to<lb/> you. I wrote to you about <persName>Mach</persName>
                                        whom I asked for<lb/> payment for the “Occident” ($6). He
                                        told me that he had re<lb/>ceived only 15 numbers and did
                                        not want to pay more<lb/> than $4. I have also written to
                                                  <persName>Mr. Mayers</persName> at
                                                  <placeName>Frankf<add>?</add><lb/>
                                                  Kentucky</placeName>, but have received no reply.
                                        You can write to<lb/> him yourself. He is in
                                                  <placeName>Kentucky</placeName>—<persName>H.
                                                  Mayers</persName>,
                                                  <placeName>Frankf<add>?</add><lb/>
                                                  Kentucky</placeName>. <persName>Mr. E.
                                                  Mach</persName> does not want to pay more
                                        than<lb/> $4. If you want to have it write to me immediately
                                        and<lb/> I shall send it at once. I know of nothing more to
                                        write at<lb/> present. I can get no subscribers for the
                                        “Occident” he<lb/> Please write to me at once.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">With best greetings,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">W. Dryfus</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
